Neurio claims to make ‘an ordinary home smart’ recognises the electronic signature of different devices . 
  The $250 (£168) device plugs into a breaker box to monitor energy consumption and can be used to control appliances remotely . 
  Neurio monitors a home around the clock and can tell users if they have left lights on . 
  It recognises different devices such as kettles and washing machines . 
  The device feeds information about energy consumption back to an app . 
  When used with another app it can turn appliances on and off remotely . 
 